name: sfchronicle
text: The number of people hospitalized with COVID-19 in California dropped for the sixth straight day, to 5,636 on Saturday. That is down from 6,362 a week earlier. https://t.co/ofct5eVW0S

name: sfchronicle
text: Who says golfers are bland and boring? The @PGAChampionship at Harding Park in San Francisco was a showcase for some pros who, on closer inspection, bring some fun to the party, says columnist @ScottOstler: https://t.co/VV3M7Wl4CS

name: sfchronicle
text: BREAKING: Sonia Angell, California’s public health officer and one of the top officials formulating the state’s response to the coronavirus pandemic, abruptly announced her resignation Sunday night. https://t.co/K6xQemCIL4

name: sfchronicle
text:
As the coronavirus enters its eighth month, young people now make up the largest and fastest-growing demographic contracting the virus in many regions.

@Cat_Ho has the full story here: https://t.co/78lTS00cDO https://t.co/kaJMpDOgS3

name: sfchronicle
text:
California has not executed a prisoner since 2006. Now coronavirus is stalking the condemned men of San Quentin’s Death Row.
